description:
Saxophonist Jimmy Greene talks about his creative process as a composer, future pieces for the Real Book and his regard for Tom Harrell in whose band Greene played.

This interview was taped backstage at the 2017 Newport Jazz Festival, where Greene performed with his quartet. It was his first time appearing there as a leader.  For more information about Greene, visit www.jimmygreene.com 

Interview by Irene Lee. Produced for JazzTimes by Lee Mergner. More info at www.jazztimes.com
